snippet: During his decades in public office, Former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. developed a unique set of phrases, dubbed “Bidenisms” by his close observers. Here’s what to watch for.

headline_main: Moderates Faltered at Tuesday’s Debate. Will Joe Biden Do Better Tonight?

snippet: The real victor in the moderates-versus-progressives battle was the moderate who wasn’t there.
lead_paragraph: Marianne Williamson won last night’s debate if you judge exclusively in terms of charisma, rhetoric and the effective use of television. Bernie Sanders and Elizabeth Warren won last night’s debate — Sanders slightly more so, in my view — if you judge based on whether the two most important candidates onstage did what they needed to remain important. John Delaney won last night’s debate, despite earning the everlasting ire of left-wing Twitter, if you want to know which also-ran candidate made the most of his chances in the spotlight.

snippet: The investment giant announced that it is becoming a C corporation and moving to a “one share, one-vote” model that could give its stock price a boost.
lead_paragraph: Good Wednesday morning. On today’s agenda: the Fed’s big announcement on interest rates. More on what to expect below. (Was this email forwarded to you? Sign up here.)
abstract: The investment giant announced that it is becoming a C corporation and moving to a “one share, one-vote” model that could give its stock price a boost.

headline_main: Where in N.Y.C. to Watch the Democratic Debate

snippet: In an extended interview, the California senator explains why she thinks litmus-test questions aren’t helpful and how she is approaching this campaign.
lead_paragraph: Senator Kamala Harris has emerged as one of the most important candidates in the Democratic primary, besting Joseph R. Biden Jr. in a debate last month and exciting liberal voters who see her as a strong challenger to President Trump. But Ms. Harris has eluded ideological definition for much of the race.
abstract: In an extended interview, the California senator explains why she thinks litmus-test questions aren’t helpful and how she is approaching this campaign.
